OL,3,CSugar tax changes: The drinks that
OL,4,Ccould be affected by the new levy
OL,6,FThe Treasury has proposed reducing the
OL,7,Fmaximum amount of sugar allowed in
OL,8,Fdrinks, bought off the shelves, before
OL,9,Fthey become subject to the levy from
OL,10,F5g to 4g per 100ml.
OL,12,FChancellor Rachel Reeves said in last
OL,13,Fyear's autumn budget the Government
OL,14,Fwould consider expanding the sugar tax
OL,15,Fto cover more drinks.
OL,17,FThe Treasury says 89% of fizzy drinks
OL,18,Fsold in the UK do not pay the tax due
OL,19,Fto widespread reformulation since the
OL,20,Flevy was first introduced.
