OL,6,F"The sugar tax has been such a
OL,7,Fdramatic failure that it should be
OL,8,Frepealed, not expanded," said
OL,9,FChristopher Snowdon, head of lifestyle
OL,10,Feconomics at the Institute.
OL,12,F"Sugar taxes have never worked
OL,13,Fanywhere. What happened to Starmer's
OL,14,Fpromise to not raise taxes on working
OL,15,Fpeople?"
OL,17,FDr Kawther Hashem of Action on Sugar
OL,18,Fat Queen Mary University of London
OL,19,Fwelcomed the plans, calling them a
OL,20,F"bold and necessary" step for public
OL,21,Fhealth.
